The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 November is 101,254 (11,670.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 November, there were 3,837 new confirmed cases (442.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 November, there were 4,754 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 19% (917 fewer cases).
